            "question": {
                "text": "For Σ={a, b}, let us consider the regular language \n\nL = {x | x = a2 + 3k or x = b10 +12k, k \\ge 0}. \n\nWhich one of the following can be a pumping length (the \nconstant guaranteed by the pumping lemma) for L?",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "3",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "5",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "9",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "24",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "D"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "L ={a2 + 3k }  {b10 + 12k} \n\n   = aa (aaa)* + b10. (b12)* \n\nNumber of states = 16 \n\nSo, pumping length must be greater than 16. \n\nHence, option (d) is correct.",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
