            "question": {
                "text": "Consider alphabet Σ = {0,1}, the null/empty string λ \nand the sets of strings X0, X1, and X2 generated by \nthe corresponding non-terminals of a regular \ngrammar. X0, X1 and X2 are related as follows: \n\nX0 = 1 X1 \n\n\nX1 = 0 X1 + 1 X2 \n\nX2 = 0 X1 + {λ} \n\nWhich one of the following choices precisely \nrepresents the strings in X0?",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "10(0* + (10)*) 1",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "10(0* + (10)*)* 1",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "1(0 + 10)* 1",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "10(0 + 10)* 1 + 110(0 +10)* 1 \n\nRegular Language Identification",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "C"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "X2 \\rightarrow 0X1 |  \n\n\n X2 = 0X1 +  \n\n X1 \\rightarrow 0X1 | 1X2 \n\n\n X1 = 0X1 | 10X1 | 1 \n\n\n X1 = (0 + 10)*1 \n\nX0 = 1X1  \n\n\n X0 = 1(0 + 10)*1 \n\nHence, option (c) is correct.",
                "images": [
                    "assets/Theory Of Computation/TOC_Regular_Language_and_Grammar_P23_X1369.png"
                ],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        },
