                    "text": "L. LR = {x y | x  L, yR L}",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "{w wR | w  L}",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "Prefix (L) = {x  * | ∃y* such that \nxyL}",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "Suffix (L) ={y  * | ∃x* such that xyL}",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "B"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "(a) If L is Regular then L.LR  is Regular. \n\n(b) May/may not be Regular over Σ = {a, b}.  \n\n If L = a* then wwR = (aa)* is regular \n\n If L = (a+b)* then wwR is not regular  \n\n(c) Prefix(Regular) is always Regular \n\n(d) Suffix(Regular) is always Regular  \n\n Hence, option (b) is correct.",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        },
