            "question": {
                "text": "Let L1 = {w  {0, 1}* | w has at least as many \noccurrences of (110)'s as (011)'s} . Let L2 = {w {0, \n1}*| w has at least as many occurrences of (000)'s as \n(111)'s}. Which one of the following is TRUE?",
                "images": [],
